4.1 We collect information about you during the account registration process for any of our Services.  This information may include, but is not limited to your name, postal address, e-mail address, phone number, credit/debit card details and any other mandatory details as might be requested from you for the purpose of registration and/or continued use of our Services.

4.2 We may also collect and process the following data about you during the course of  your use of our Services:
(a) if you contact us, we may keep a record of that correspondence;
(b) your entry details for a competition or promotion;
(c) details of your visits to our Services and the resources and webpages that you access including, without limitation, traffic data, location data and other communication data (including IP address).  We do not extract any personal information (e.g. email address or name) that may be in a web browser's user preference file;
(d) technical information relating to the device that you use to access our Services;
(e) information and communications on forums on the Websites, including chat rooms and message boards;
(f) information we collect using cookies stored on your device about how you use our Services and/or selected third party websites.  For more information on cookies please refer to section 8 below;
(g) where you communicate or share information with Us or other users of our Services through player forums, message boards, profile comments, in-game challenges and chat messaging with game operators or other users;
(h) your telephone conversations - either to place a bet or a customer service call - these may be recorded both to assist us in training and in quality management, and to allow for the speedy resolution of queries; and
(i) your betting, gaming, payments and other account transactions – these are routinely analysed so as to assist us in improving the Services we provide to you.

You acknowledge and consent to the recording and retention of such information for these purposes.

4.3 Our Services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18 and we do not knowingly record or retain any personal information from such individuals. In the event that we inadvertently gather personal information in relation to a minor, we will take reasonable measures to promptly close any relevant accounts and remove any records where possible, other than such information as will allow us to identify and prevent future access from such individuals.

5.1 The information that we collect is used by Us in order to process your transactions and requests and for any other purposes set out herein.  This processing includes, in certain circumstances, the transfer of your information to our third party data processors who assist with the performance of certain Services or elements thereof.  Your information may be processed in the following ways:

(a) for general account management and processing of your transactions via your banking service provider;
(b) for the provision of betting services;
(c) to help identify you;
(d) to verify your age and accuracy of your registration details, including disclosure of such information to third parties e.g. financial institutions and third party reference agencies;
(e) to serve appropriate and tailored marketing material and content via SMS, email, phone, push notification, post or otherwise, in accordance with your marketing preferences;
(f) to help diagnose system problems and to administer our Website;
(g) to gather broad demographic information about you, such as determining whether you are a user from outside the UK;
(h) to monitor and improve our Services;
(i) to carry out customer research, testing and analysis;
(j) to carry out risk management;
(k) to detect and report fraud, cheating and money laundering; and
(l) to enable us to comply with any legal or regulatory requirements.

6.1 As with any social network, please be aware that the Facebook In-Play App involves the sharing of certain data with the rest of the community in that network.

6.2 For users of the Facebook In-Play App we may also collect and process, as allowed by you through the Facebook App authentication process, certain additional information from Facebook, including;

(a) Your first and last name;
(b) Your profile picture or its URL;
(c) Your user ID number, which is linked to publicly available information as name and profile photo;
(d) The user ID numbers and other public data of your friends;
(e) The login email you provided to Facebook when you registered;
(f) Your physical location and that of your access devices;
(g) Your likes and your friends likes;
(h) Your gender; and
(i) Your date of birth.

6.3 For users of the Facebook In-Play App we may also share or notify your information, as authorised by you through the App and Facebook settings, through a number of features within the App and via auto-posting to your Facebook profile. The App may restrict the quantity of notifications that are posted on a daily basis so each In-Play activity may not automatically be posted to your profile. Notification types will include, but are not limited to:

(a) Bet placement (including those where a free bet is used);
(b) Bet win (including single and multiple bets;
(c) Challenges submitted, won and lost;
(d) New followers; and
(e) Player profile heat index changes.

6.4 We consider elements of the data outlined in 6.2 and 6.3 above to be public information, which may be accessed by the rest of the community, including your friends, followers or other users of the App. However, we also treat certain other information as private, which will never be visible or accessible to the rest of the community. This private information includes your account balance, bet stake amount, winning or loss amount for any bet.

6.5 Any user of the App can choose to follow you. Where someone chooses to follow you, you will receive an individual notification to this effect within the App. You do not have the ability to restrict or control which individuals are permitted to follow you. Your followers, friends and other users of the In-Play App will have the ability to access your In-Play profile and public information including details of challenges, awards, heat index, your position on leaderboards, a limited view of your betting history, competition standings and achievements.

6.6 If you do not wish to share certain data with the community and the existing control settings within the In-Play App or Facebook do not enable you to restrict that sharing, please discontinue your use of this service and we suggest instead that you use our other non-social networking Services such as www.paddypower.com.
